  "texts": [
    "• Alignment-tuning: LLMs can sometimes produce inaccurate or harmful content.",
    "To address this, alignmenttuning is conducted using human feedback to adjust outputs and discourage undesirable responses.",
    "This process ensures models align with ethical standards, characterized by the \"HHH\" criteria: helpful, honest, and harmless (Askell et al., 2021).",
    "Techniques such as reinforcement learning with human feedback (RLHF) (Ziegler et al., 2019) are employed, where models are refined through reward modeling (RM) and reinforcement learning (RL) to meet these criteria.",
    "After an LLM has been thoroughly trained and finetuned, the prompting technique is employed to elicit responses from the LLM."
  ],
